lambda expressions with functional interfaces example:

Implementing Runnable interface using LambdaExpressions:

public class Test {

	public static void main(String[] args) {

		Runnable r = () -> {

			System.out.println("Thread started");
		};

		Thread t = new Thread(r);

		t.start();
	}

}

lambda expressions without braces when passing arguments


If you observed below code i have removed () while passing arguments , so we can understand these () are not mandatory while passing arguments 

interface Light {

	public void switchOn(boolean bool);
}

public class Test {

	public static void main(String[] args) {

		Light light = l -> System.out.println("is light turned on:" + l);

		light.switchOn(true);

	}

}


